Every resident of Kalmykia is a debtor
Residents of the republic are increasingly visiting the official website of the Office of the Federal Service of bailiffs of Russia for the Republic of Kazakhstan.
According to the specialists of the department of organizational and control work, informatization and information security of the republican department, over the past eight months, more than 140,000 visits to the site itself, more than 42,000 visits to the section "Bank of data of executive proceedings", 661 payment receipts for payment of debts were downloaded.
According to the Chairman of the Public Council at the UFSP of Russia for the Republic of Kazakhstan Valery Bogdanov, almost every resident of the region has debts for utility payments, traffic police fines, bank loans, loans, and no one is immune from unforeseen situations.
But debtors can expect negative consequences in the form of, for example, a ban on traveling abroad.
That is why the UFSSP of Russia recommends that everyone who plans a trip abroad, clarify in the department of bailiffs at the place of residence or on the website www.r08fssprus.ru information about the presence of unpaid debts and repay them.
The service created a "Bank of data of executive proceedings" for the convenience of citizens.
This special electronic application is available not only on the regional websites of UFSSP of Russia, but also in social networks and mobile communication means iPad, iPhone and smartphone.
The data bank contains information on enforcement proceedings initiated by the Kalmyk bailiffs against all debtors, - explains the assistant head of the UFSSSP of Russia for the Republic of Kazakhstan Delgir Bodgaeva.
"In the presence of debts, the system displays information on the number and date of initiation of enforcement proceedings; the name of the body that issued the executive letter or other act; its number, amount and type of debt; the address of the bailiffs' department; the name of the bailiff; contact phone number.
Information on the progress of enforcement proceedings can also be obtained on the portal of public services at: http://epgu.gosuslugi.ru"
